<p><emph render="bold"> <ref actuate="onrequest" show="replace" target="s1">Series I. Brooklyn Bridge</ref> </emph></p><p> <emph render="bold"> <ref actuate="onrequest" show="replace" target="s2">Series II. Other New York Landmarks</ref> </emph></p>  </arrangement>
  <separatedmaterial id="aspace_92859f14573c142106534b950adead72">
    <head>SEPARATED MATERIAL</head>
    <list type="ordered">
      <head>Books</head>
      <item>Brooklyn Bridge 1883-1933. A valuable history published to commemorate the 50th anniversary of the Brooklyn Bridge. First Edition.</item>
      <item>Opening Ceremonies of the New York and Brooklyn Bridge. 1883. Inscribed on flyleaf by Emily Warren Roebling, wife of Chief Engineer Washington Roebling. Rudin # M-48A</item>
      <item>The New York City Subway: Its Construction and Equipment. Inscription reads "Presented to Alderman John H. Dougherty, by August Belmont, Esq. President, Interborough Rapid Transit Company, November 21st, 1904". Rudin # M-94</item>
